---
/**
 * Three-column feature grid: Remember, Recall, Blame. Each column
 * pairs a CLI snippet with the matching MCP tool name so readers see
 * "this is how you do it from a shell" and "this is what the model
 * calls it" at the same glance.
 *
 * Card accent colors match the pillar mapping from the hero:
 *   Remember → blue    (stateful)
 *   Recall   → green   (topic-matched)
 *   Blame    → amber   (inspectable)
 */
---

<section class="section features">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">
			<span class="eyebrow-text">THREE_VERBS //</span>
		</div>
		<h2 class="section-title">Three verbs. That's the whole product.</h2>
		<p class="section-lede">
			CTXone boils down to three things an AI tool does to memory.
			Everything else — branches, priming, session stats, provenance
			— falls out of these.
		</p>

		<div class="grid">
			<article class="card card-blue">
				<div class="card-label">01 // REMEMBER</div>
				<h3>Remember</h3>
				<p>
					Write a fact once. It survives sessions, branches, and tool
					switches. Importance maps to a confidence score so
					high-value facts aren't drowned out by chatter.
				</p>
				<pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> ctx remember "BSL-1.1 for all new repos" \
    --importance high --context licensing

<span class="comment"># from an LLM:</span>
remember(fact="BSL-1.1 for all new repos",
         importance="high", context="licensing")</code></pre>
			</article>

			<article class="card card-green">
				<div class="card-label">02 // RECALL</div>
				<h3>Recall</h3>
				<p>
					Ask a topic. Get pinned context plus relevant facts,
					capped at a token budget. Every response includes the
					live savings ratio so the claim is provable in real
					time.
				</p>
				<pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> ctx recall "licensing" --budget 1500

<span class="comment"># from an LLM:</span>
recall(topic="licensing", budget=1500)</code></pre>
			</article>

			<article class="card card-amber">
				<div class="card-label">03 // BLAME</div>
				<h3>Blame</h3>
				<p>
					Every commit carries an agent ID, a timestamp, an intent,
					and optional reasoning. <code>ctx blame</code> traces a
					fact back to the tool, user, and session that wrote it.
				</p>
				<pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> ctx blame /memory/legal/bsl

<span class="comment"># who wrote it, when, and why:</span>
agent:  claude-code
when:   2026-03-14T09:17:23Z
intent: Observe
reason: user preference</code></pre>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.features {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 70% 40% at 50% 100%,
				rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.04),
				transparent 60%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.28);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.eyebrow-text {
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.card {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;
		transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
	}

	.card::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		height: 3px;
	}

	.card-blue::before {
		background: var(--ctx-accent);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.5);
	}

	.card-green::before {
		background: var(--ctx-success);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.5);
	}

	.card-amber::before {
		background: var(--ctx-warn);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(252, 211, 77, 0.5);
	}

	.card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
	}

	.card-label {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.card-blue .card-label {
		color: var(--ctx-accent);
	}

	.card-green .card-label {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
	}

	.card-amber .card-label {
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
	}

	.card h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.85rem 0;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	.card p {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	.card p code {
		background: #0a0a0a;
		padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-sm);
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: var(--ctx-warn);
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.card pre {
		background: #050505;
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border-lo);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-md);
		padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
		color: var(--ctx-text);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	.card pre code {
		background: transparent;
		padding: 0;
		color: inherit;
	}

	.prompt {
		color: var(--ctx-success);
		user-select: none;
	}

	.comment {
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
